Executive Profile
Robert J. Weiland  Chief Commercial Officer, Pacira Pharmaceuticals, Inc.AgeTotal Calculated CompensationThis person is connected to 1 Board Members in 1 different organizations across 4 different industries.See Board Relationships57$1,924,578As of Fiscal Year 2016
Background

		Mr. Robert J. Weiland, also known as Bob, has been Chief Commercial Officer at Pacira Pharmaceuticals, Inc. since April 5, 2016. Mr. Weiland served as Vice President of Operations of Takeda Pharmaceuticals North America, Inc. (now known as Takeda Pharmaceuticals U.S.A., Inc.). Mr. Weiland directed many of Takeda's key functions, including supply chain, trade and corporate services and a centralized analytics group, which is housed under the department. He served as Vice ... President and General Manager of Surgery Business Unit of The Medicines Co. since August 2004. Mr. Weiland led an organization responsible for building the Medicines's second therapeutic business unit with two major surgical products in clinical development including overseeing Phase 3 clinical trials and pre-launch activities. Previously, Mr. Weiland worked at Abbott Laboratories for 14 years, holding key leadership positions in a variety of sales, marketing and business development roles, in both domestic and international businesses. He also held marketing and sales positions at Tenneco and American Hospital Supply, Inc., earlier in his career. He has been a Director of Cymabay Therapeutics, Inc., since April 2016. Mr. Weiland earned a bachelor's degree from DeSales University and a master's in business administration from the Wharton School of the University of Pennsylvania.Read Full Background




